Notebook[{
Cell["WolframChallengesBenchmark \[LongDash] Tutorial", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"4bd4582b-f865-4d2f-a2f7-8eb9e030ab64"],

Cell["\<\
This tutorial walks through the end-to-end workflow for grading LLM-generated \
Wolfram Language solutions with the ChallengesBenchmark harness: loading a \
test bank, running a model's solutions under isolation + sandbox, inspecting \
typed results, rendering reports (including JUnit XML for CI), authoring your \
own tests in the .wlchallenge format, auditing a solutions directory, and \
comparing two model runs.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a675f9b2-b11d-4123-a112-136fcb2c30c1"],

Cell["\<\
The harness is a regular Wolfram paclet. Every example in this notebook runs \
in-process against a tiny synthetic test bank so you can follow along without \
a pre-existing solutions directory.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"7441f271-f6b2-41b6-80c4-cd35465a2027"],

Cell["1. Setup", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"d91d660f-e9df-4e34-b243-61f2161194b5"],

Cell["\<\
Point $Path at the repo root (the folder holding the ChallengesBenchmark/ \
directory), then Get the package. If you opened this notebook from the repo, \
the default below works out-of-the-box.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d7b03408-372b-432f-a46f-f94d3a0a8641"],

Cell["\<\
$repoRoot = If[$Notebooks, NotebookDirectory[] /. $Failed :> Directory[], \
Directory[]];
$repoRoot = FileNameDrop[$repoRoot, -1]; (* docs/ -> repo root *)
PrependTo[$Path, $repoRoot];
Get[\"ChallengesBenchmark`ChallengesBenchmark`\"];
Names[\"ChallengesBenchmark`*\"] // Sort\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"8498077f-2c13-4b21-906d-33a089c91cb8"],

Cell["\<\
The package exposes a loader/runner/report group of functions plus a \
.wlchallenge authoring group. Key public entry points:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"7904f8e2-5d0d-4e39-8245-f7e992cecce7"],

Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
   "LoadChallenges", " ", "\[CenterDot]", " ", "LoadTestBank", " ", "\[CenterDot]",
     " ", "LoadSolutions"}], " ", "\[LongDash]", " ", 
   RowBox[{"import", " ", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"inputs", ".", "\n", "ExtractCode"}], " ", "\[CenterDot]", " ", 
     "SaveSolution", " ", "\[CenterDot]", " ", "AuditSolutions"}]}], " ", "\[LongDash]",
    " ", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"work", " ", "with", " ", "per"}], "-", 
    RowBox[{"model", " ", "solutions", " ", "on", " ", 
     RowBox[{"disk", ".", "\n", "RunBenchmark"}]}]}], " ", "\[LongDash]", " ", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"the", " ", "runner"}], ";", " ", 
    RowBox[{"returns", " ", 
     RowBox[{"a", " ", "'"}], 
     RowBox[{"run", "'"}], " ", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"Association", ".", "\n", "WriteReport"}], " ", "\[CenterDot]", 
      " ", "WriteJUnitReport"}]}]}], " ", "\[LongDash]", " ", 
   RowBox[{"render", " ", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"html", "/", "md"}], "/", "json"}], "/", 
      RowBox[{"junit", ".", "\n", "DiffRuns"}]}], " ", "\[CenterDot]", " ", 
     "CompareModels", " ", "\[CenterDot]", " ", "WriteCompareReport"}]}], " ",
    "\[LongDash]", " ", 
   RowBox[{"cross", "-", 
    RowBox[{"run", " ", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"analysis", ".", "\n", "LoadWLChallenge"}], " ", "\[CenterDot]",
       " ", "BuildTestBank", " ", "\[CenterDot]", " ", "WriteTestBankFiles", 
      " ", "\[CenterDot]", " ", "WriteWLChallengeDir"}]}]}], " ", "\[LongDash]",
    " ", 
   RowBox[{"plain", "-", 
    RowBox[{"text", " ", 
     RowBox[{"authoring", "."}]}]}]}], Code]], "Text",ExpressionUUID->\
"22a4df16-2f30-45c0-84f3-af4b0e9a7503"],

Cell["2. A minimal benchmark run", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"d48d5bce-cc7d-45a0-aeb2-475ae2953275"],

Cell["\<\
A 'test bank' is an Association mapping challenge names to lists of test \
entries. Each entry carries a held input (so the candidate function can be \
undefined at author time), the expected result, and optional metadata.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"fe970907-214c-4642-acf6-27c1909f11a4"],

Cell["\<\
miniBank = <|
  \"DoublePlusOne\" -> {
    <|\"challengeName\" -> \"DoublePlusOne\", \"testIndex\" -> 1,
      \"input\" -> HoldComplete[DoublePlusOne[3]], \"expected\" -> 7,
      \"metadata\" -> <||>|>,
    <|\"challengeName\" -> \"DoublePlusOne\", \"testIndex\" -> 2,
      \"input\" -> HoldComplete[DoublePlusOne[10]], \"expected\" -> 21,
      \"metadata\" -> <||>|>
  },
  \"Reverse\" -> {
    <|\"challengeName\" -> \"Reverse\", \"testIndex\" -> 1,
      \"input\" -> HoldComplete[MyReverse[{1, 2, 3}]], \"expected\" -> {3, 2, \
1},
      \"metadata\" -> <||>|>
  }
|>;
Length[miniBank]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"c4e3dd38-3cf5-4410-8c45-478d3aa7643d"],

Cell["\<\
'Solutions' is an Association mapping challenge names to {'code' -> <string>} \
records. The code string defines the function(s) the test inputs call.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"9867dfc8-ab83-470a-8be4-8081a6902b77"],

Cell["\<\
miniSolutions = <|
  \"DoublePlusOne\" -> <|
    \"code\" -> \"DoublePlusOne[x_] := 2 x + 1\",
    \"metadata\" -> <||>
  |>,
  \"Reverse\" -> <|
    \"code\" -> \"MyReverse[xs_] := Reverse[xs]\",
    \"metadata\" -> <||>
  |>
|>;\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"4b44cfe2-ea2d-47d8-85c3-9c62a4d46dd2"],

Cell["\<\
Run. IsolationMode -> 'InProcess' is fastest (uses the driver kernel) but \
offers no safety against candidate Abort/Quit \[LongDash] use it only for \
self-tests. The default 'PerTestKernel' launches a fresh subkernel per test \
via LocalSubmit.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"b04843f3-f8dc-4871-a407-83f297942e6b"],

Cell["\<\
tmpOut = CreateDirectory[];
run = RunBenchmark[
  <||>, miniBank, miniSolutions,
  \"Model\"           -> \"tutorial-demo\",
  \"OutputDirectory\" -> tmpOut,
  \"IsolationMode\"   -> \"InProcess\",
  \"Parallel\"        -> 1,
  \"TimeConstraint\"  -> 5
];
Keys[run]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"b9579b77-92f2-4254-af6b-a1cca6975da1"],

Cell["3. Reading the run Association", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"14664557-da5f-497f-b97b-51d331f97310"],

Cell["\<\
`run[\"meta\"]` holds the header: runId, model, runtime fingerprint, options \
used, and a summary. `run[\"results\"]` is the per-test list.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"2c3001b0-e38f-4319-a9c9-e90214fc5b25"],

Cell["run[\"meta\", \"summary\"]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"5a23e059-06f3-445f-a256-1b381a980b4d"],

Cell["\<\
(* Per-test result records all share the same shape *)
First[run[\"results\"]] // Keys\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"8d8a1f87-0b8c-4f8e-8d85-2d8096f62b27"],

Cell["\<\
(* The 'status' field classifies what happened, independent of pass/fail *)
Tally[#[\"status\"] & /@ run[\"results\"]]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"d79ff81d-6450-4865-8d49-54d9c910a402"],

Cell["\<\
Status codes: 'Evaluated' (ran to completion; `passed` is meaningful), \
'TimedOut', 'MemoryExceeded', 'EvaluationError', 'ParseError', 'NoSolution', \
'KernelDied', 'RunnerError'. Only Evaluated results can pass.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"9ccc8d6d-64e8-4dad-a697-3109a147fb95"],

Cell["4. Rendering reports", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"8ca38c83-59ca-4ca4-87c3-b30452b8573e"],

Cell["\<\
WriteReport drops four files into the run directory: report.html (a styled \
dashboard), report.md (Markdown summary), report.json (machine-readable) and \
junit.xml (for CI).\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"23a3e702-8c4a-47d7-a03f-008a096fda89"],

Cell["\<\
paths = WriteReport[run, run[\"runDir\"]];
Association[paths]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"e07c2f7f-31c9-4b17-8f11-3bb9fc94c847"],

Cell["\<\
(* Peek at the Markdown summary *)
StringTake[Import[paths[\"markdown\"], \"Text\"], UpTo[600]]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"d7469e0e-f37c-4481-a4f6-8cb29aeeff32"],

Cell["\<\
(* The JUnit XML is well-formed and consumable by GitHub Actions,
   Jenkins xUnit, GitLab's test reporter, etc. *)
StringTake[Import[paths[\"junit\"], \"Text\"], UpTo[500]]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"913d3397-7233-4c75-9911-7ef36a9d0daf"],

Cell["5. Authoring tests: the .wlchallenge format", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"57a4e800-7e24-4f3e-b37c-be6433a1014f"],

Cell["\<\
`ChallengesTests.wxf` + `ChallengesTestDataV1.json` are the compiled runtime \
bank. They are built from a directory of plain-text `.wlchallenge` files, one \
per challenge, which are diffable and easy to edit.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"58ce1701-7979-4870-a50b-fb571f23042e"],

Cell["\<\
wlcDir = CreateDirectory[];
aliquotPath = FileNameJoin[{wlcDir, \"aliquot.wlchallenge\"}];
Export[aliquotPath,
  StringJoin[
    \"(* :Name: AliquotSequence *)\\n\",
    \"(* :Index: 1 *)\\n\",
    \"(* :Instruction: Write Wolfram Language code that performs the \
following task *)\\n\",
    \"\\n\",
    \"(* :Prompt: *)\\n\",
    \"Define AliquotSequence[n] returning the aliquot sequence starting at n,\
\\n\",
    \"terminating once it reaches 1 or enters a cycle.\\n\",
    \"\\n\",
    \"(* :Tests: *)\\n\",
    \"{AliquotSequence[20], {20, 22, 14, 10, 8, 7, 1}}\\n\",
    \"{AliquotSequence[6],  {6}}\\n\"
  ],
  \"Text\"];
FileByteCount[aliquotPath]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"16d3e871-7d98-4f89-8016-8d1b2ad5fb24"],

Cell["\<\
LoadWLChallenge parses one file; LoadChallengesDir loads an entire directory. \
Inputs come back as HoldComplete[expr] so the parser never evaluates \
candidate-facing code.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"95d22d7c-9a15-4561-93d5-1d4660e98927"],

Cell["\<\
entry = LoadWLChallenge[aliquotPath];
<| \"name\" -> entry[\"name\"], \"index\" -> entry[\"index\"],
   \"testCount\" -> Length[entry[\"tests\"]],
   \"firstInputHead\" -> Head[entry[\"tests\"][[1, 1]]] |>\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"1f23c33d-6894-4da3-a8fb-6741b6f60faf"],

Cell["\<\
BuildTestBank returns the pair { challengesAssoc, testBankAssoc } in the \
shape the runtime uses. WriteTestBankFiles additionally exports the legacy \
JSON + WXF.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"0d668b0e-85b4-48f0-b0c5-2b1605879e31"],

Cell["\<\
{challenges, bank} = BuildTestBank[wlcDir];
Length /@ {challenges, bank}\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"4354c015-92bc-43be-bc0b-11afe5cc439d"],

Cell["\<\
compileOut = CreateDirectory[];
WriteTestBankFiles[wlcDir,
  FileNameJoin[{compileOut, \"ChallengesTestDataV1.json\"}],
  FileNameJoin[{compileOut, \"ChallengesTests.wxf\"}]]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"a6d2e787-27a4-45b3-8b16-415d194c83da"],

Cell["\<\
From the command line:

  wolframscript -file scripts/BuildTestBank.wls --in .challenges --json \
ChallengesTestDataV1.json --wxf ChallengesTests.wxf

Add --reverse to seed a .wlchallenge directory from an existing compiled \
bank. The CLI post-verifies that the file it just wrote re-parses to \
identical counts.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"73286238-3a3b-401e-9cd2-3d093d9b6c55"],

Cell["6. Auditing a solutions directory", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"3daf03ad-f70b-42ec-badc-906a1967c395"],

Cell["\<\
Before running, you can audit a `solutions/<model>/` directory against the \
test bank: AuditSolutions parses each file structurally (never evaluates it) \
and reports missing files, unexpected extras, mismatched function names, \
parse failures, and empty code. This catches mislabeled files early.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"99e7895d-dda5-4c0a-8513-0be72e2d7585"],

Cell["\<\
solDir = CreateDirectory[];
Export[FileNameJoin[{solDir, \"DoublePlusOne.wl\"}],
  \"DoublePlusOne[x_] := 2 x + 1\", \"Text\"];
Export[FileNameJoin[{solDir, \"Reverse.wl\"}],
  \"MyReverse[xs_] := Reverse[xs]\", \"Text\"];
AuditSolutions[solDir, miniBank]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"1661aec5-eafe-47ac-a5cf-df1d806ac41b"],

Cell["\<\
SaveSolution also runs the audit at write-time if you pass the test bank as a \
4th argument, and refuses to write the file if the code doesn't define any of \
the expected names.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"008d5701-18d8-4a5c-b42e-631ec7fdf65b"],

Cell["7. Comparing model runs", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"97298a88-2142-491d-8126-24840a656415"],

Cell["\<\
CompareModels takes a list of run directories (or an Association mapping \
display labels to directories) and produces a cross-model report: per-model \
pass rates, a per-challenge pass matrix, and 'uniquely passed / uniquely \
failed' per model.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"7d63f59f-ac5c-4c2c-8a4b-57e9d1ef5a91"],

Cell["\<\
WriteCompareReport emits compare.md and compare.html so you can publish the \
comparison alongside the individual run reports.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"58f0e86b-4fb4-42e2-b524-68bef482ae54"],

Cell["\<\
(* Example (pseudocode):

    cmp = CompareModels[{
      \"runs/run-2026-04-01-abc123\",
      \"runs/run-2026-04-02-def456\"
    }];
    WriteCompareReport[cmp, \"runs/compare-apr\"]
*)\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"96df7b1a-1666-439a-93da-b3e382573957"],

Cell["8. Regression detection with DiffRuns", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"ec2739d7-9b11-46e7-8a23-bc99fdc738d1"],

Cell["\<\
DiffRuns structurally compares a new run against a baseline and returns \
`regressions` (newly-failing tests), `fixes` (newly-passing tests) and \
`unchanged`. The CLI exposes this via `--baseline` and exits with code 3 when \
any regression appears, which is the hook CI systems use to block merges.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a76dd309-3e18-4b9e-acd3-2ce9a0b62f2d"],

Cell["9. From the command line", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"ae855c2a-2104-4253-8a6b-b96156642f3e"],

Cell["The full CLI surface for a CI-friendly run:", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"ee42c963-d39a-4d6a-9f49-29d4453ae4a3"],

Cell["\<\
wolframscript -file scripts/RunBenchmark.wls \\
  --challenges ChallengesTestDataV1.json \\
  --testbank   ChallengesTests.wxf \\
  --solutions  solutions/claude-opus-4.6 \\
  --model      claude-opus-4.6 \\
  --out        runs \\
  --parallel   8 \\
  --timeout    60 \\
  --memory     2000000000 \\
  --isolation  PerTestKernel \\
  --sandbox    true \\
  --verify-solutions --strict-verify \\
  --junit      ci/junit.xml \\
  --baseline   runs/run-2026-04-01-abc123 \\
  --fail-under 0.65\
\>", "Program",ExpressionUUID->"aad444ad-d1fb-4cc2-9d6b-eec0ff5fba6d"],

Cell["\<\
Exit codes: 0 = ok, 1 = bad args, 2 = pass rate under threshold, 3 = \
regressions, 4 = unexpected error, 5 = strict-verify failed.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"0ef0acaa-8254-4de2-bf53-2868dc19a351"],

Cell["10. Cleanup", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"639a1aee-1297-48eb-b0cb-8900894a6029"],

Cell["\<\
Quiet @ DeleteDirectory[tmpOut,      DeleteContents -> True];
Quiet @ DeleteDirectory[wlcDir,      DeleteContents -> True];
Quiet @ DeleteDirectory[compileOut,  DeleteContents -> True];
Quiet @ DeleteDirectory[solDir,      DeleteContents -> True];\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"8d7b761a-aa46-4d2d-a91c-9e39e67572e5"],

Cell["Further reading", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"27593910-f8cf-47e0-ae11-dac7a58ad59e"],

Cell["\<\
\[Bullet] docs/WLCHALLENGE-FORMAT.md \[LongDash] grammar of the authoring \
format.
\[Bullet] AUDIT.md \[LongDash] pre-refactor architecture audit.
\[Bullet] ALTERNATIVE_TESTS.md \[LongDash] design notes on test primitives & \
monitoring.
\[Bullet] tests/BenchmarkTests.wlt \[LongDash] the harness's own \
VerificationTest suite; doubles as runnable documentation for every public \
function.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"bec1537e-1812-421e-97be-784a52e5f78d"]
},
